	<main>
		<img width="1500" height="720" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist.jpg 1500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-narwhal-dentist-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">The narwhal’s impressive tusk is a tooth that can sense salt, temperature, and pressure. Photo by Joseph Meehan for Narwhal Tusk Research</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Meet the Narwhal Dentist</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Dentist Martin Nweeia has a side passion for one of the weirdest teeth on the planet—the narwhal tusk.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/nicola-jones/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Nicola Jones</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						July 8, 2024 | 2,200 words, about 11 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
